UPDATED: JAN 9, 2017 Rating #1700, bottle at BKL16, "Blend 0615". Dark brown color with beige head. Aroma is sticky piney, caramel, honey. Taste is dark, honey, piney, chocolate, very thick and rich. Incredibly silky mouthfeel, hardly any carbonation. Bevog at its best, once more;

Blend 0615, tap at Borefts 2016: still excellent;

Blend 0615, bottle in December 2016: disappointing, a bit oxidized, and overall a bit bland.
